Such a sweet moment serenading Melody in San Diego yesterday. She’s an amazing young girl who is such a fighter. A sweet fan @soohyunhoneykim saw Melody and her mom @karikami_5 watching my IG live a few weeks back. Soohyun reached out to me and asked me to go serenade Melody and her family who she didn’t even know personally. She graciously said she would cover any cost. What an angel to make this happen for sweet Melody❤️❤️ Please pray for for this special family and consider donating to Melodys Go Fund Me which I’ll link in my IG story’s. If you know someone who needs this message me🙏🏻

✨ Our Tree ✨🥰🥹🌲 We spent the afternoon decorating and it made our hearts so happy! I love pulling out all the heirloom ornaments and telling their stories. Setting up the tree a little early just brings joy and sparkle to these early winter nights and we love it 🤍 (I grew up listening to Amy Grant Christmas CDs as we decorated our tree so I had to use this nostalgic song 🥹)

Gotta watch this one all the way through, loved sharing this special time with them. A friend @sharonboone7511 said this family could really use a serenade. @ms_brown_suga_3 his fiance has had a really tough time keeping the family going after he suffered a stroke and bleeding on his brain. Lashawn said my music literally got them through some really tough times, as they listened to my live IG serenades.
